  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All patients booked for an HTO due to OA

          -  Grades II to IV severity of OA by radiographic evaluation (Kellgren &amp; Lawrence grade)

          -  OA of the knee primarily involving the medial compartment

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Imaging evidence of significant knee joint pathology that would change the decision to
             do an HTO

          -  An arthroscopy of the knee within 2 years of planned surgery

          -  Active joint or systemic infection,

          -  Major medical illness that would preclude undergoing surgery,

          -  Patients who are unwilling or unable to be assessed according to study protocol for
             two years following surgery

          -  Major psychiatric illness, developmental handicap or inability to read and understand
             the English language
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
